---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const updated = "27 June 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use — Rosewood Living"
  description="The terms governing your use of the Rosewood Living website and the Letter of Intent it generates."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <!-- HEADER -->
    <section class="border-b border-line bg-surface">
      <div class="u-container pb-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem)] pt-36">
        <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="mt-6 text-h1 font-display" style="font-weight:500">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[0.9rem] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted">
          Last updated {updated}
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BODY -->
    <section class="py-[clamp(3rem,6vw,5rem)]">
      <div class="u-container">
        <article class="legal max-w-3xl">
          <p>
            These Terms of Use (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your access to and use of the Rosewood
            Living website (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;) and any materials it generates, including the
            Letter of Intent. By using the Site, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree,
            please do not use the Site.
          </p>

          <h2>1. About us</h2>
          <p>
            The Site is operated by Rosewood Living (ABN 11 142 441 549), a community and affordable
            housing management and advisory provider based in New South Wales, Australia.
          </p>

          <h2>2. The Letter of Intent</h2>
          <p>
            The Letter of Intent generated through the Site is provided as a non-binding expression
            of intent to support your planning and feasibility process. It is not a contract, offer,
            or guarantee, and does not create any legal or financial obligation on Rosewood Living or
            on you. Any engagement to provide services will be set out in a separate written
            agreement.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are responsible for ensuring the information you submit is accurate and complete. The
            generated document reflects the details you provide and should be reviewed before it is
            relied upon or included in any development application.
          </p>

          <h2>3. No professional advice</h2>
          <p>
            The content on the Site and within the Letter of Intent is general in nature and does not
            constitute legal, financial, planning or investment advice. You should obtain your own
            independent professional advice before making decisions about your project.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>use the Site for any unlawful purpose or in breach of these Terms;</li>
            <li>submit false, misleading or fraudulent information;</li>
            <li>interfere with or attempt to gain unauthorised access to the Site, its systems or data; or</li>
            <li>copy, reproduce or exploit any part of the Site for commercial purposes without our consent.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            All content on the Site — including text, branding, logos, design and the Rosewood Living
            name — is owned by or licensed to us and is protected by intellectual property laws. You
            may use the Letter of Intent we generate for you for its intended purpose, but you may not
            otherwise reproduce or distribute our content without permission.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Availability</h2>
          <p>
            We aim to keep the Site available and accurate but provide it on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and
            &ldquo;as available&rdquo; basis. We do not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted,
            error-free, or that any defects will be corrected.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Rosewood Living is not liable for any loss or
            damage arising from your use of, or reliance on, the Site or the Letter of Intent. Nothing
            in these Terms excludes any rights or guarantees you have under the Australian Consumer Law
            that cannot lawfully be excluded.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Your use of the Site is also governed by our
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, which explains how we handle your personal
            information.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Changes to these Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. The current version will always be available
            on this page, with the &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date revised accordingly. Continued use
            of the Site after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia, and you submit to the
            non-exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of that State.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Contact us</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Rosewood Living</strong><br />
            238 Victoria Rd, Gladesville NSW 2111, Australia<br />
            Email: <a href="mailto:info@rosewoodliving.com.au">info@rosewoodliving.com.au</a><br />
            ABN 11 142 441 549
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .legal > p:first-child {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--text-h3);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-top: 2.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .legal p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
  }
  .legal ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.15rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--color-rosewood);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--color-rosewood-deep);
  }
  .legal strong {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal em {
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
